-- Discover Financial profit falls 6 percent 
-- 
-- Tue Apr 22, 2014 04:14PM EDT
-- None



April 22 (Reuters) - Credit card issuer Discover Financial Services <DFS.N> reported a 6 percent fall in quarterly profit, hurt by higher provision for loan losses.

Net income allocated to common stockholders fell to $618 million, or $1.31 per share, in the first quarter ended March 31, from $659 million, or $1.33 per share, a year earlier. Revenue, net of interest expense, rose 4 percent to $2.08  billion. [ID:nBw4cKdYpa]